2.4.10-test4 hangs my machine when probing for IDE drives at boot.  The
boot messages are
Uniform Multi-Platform E-IDE driver Revision: 6.31
ide: Assuming 33MHz system bus speed for PIO modes; override with idebus=xx
ALI15X3: IDE controller on PCI bus 00 dev 70
PCI: Assigned IRQ14 for device 00:0e:0
ALI15X3: chipset revision 193
ALI15X3: not 100% native mode: will probe irqs later
ALI15X3: simplex device: DMA disabled
ide0: ALI15X3 Bus-Master DMA disabled (BIOS)
ALI15X3: simplex device: DMA disabled
ide1: ALI15X3 Bus-Master DMA disabled (BIOS)
hda: FUJITSU MPE3204AT, ATA DISK drive
hda: IRQ probe failed (0xffff9ff8)
hdb: IRQ probe failed (0xffff9ff8)
hdb: IRQ probe failed (0xffff9ff8)
hdd: SAMSUNG DVD-ROM SD-606, ATAPI CDROM drive
At this point it hangs solidly and I have to hit the reset button.
The output from lspci is
00:00.0 Host bridge: Acer Laboratories Inc. M1541 (rev 04)
00:01.0 PCI bridge: Acer Laboratories Inc. M5243 (rev 04)
00:02.0 USB Controller: Acer Laboratories Inc. M5237 (rev 03)
00:07.0 ISA bridge: Acer Laboratories Inc. M1533 (rev c3)
00:0e.0 IDE interface: Acer Laboratories Inc. M5229 (rev c1)
Test9 also hangs.  Test2 works.  I don't have any other 2.4 kernels
around to try.
